					<span class="label"><a name="footnote17-10711_000_036">17.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/5.28?lang=eng#27" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matthew 5:28</a>; see also <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/39.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 39:9</a>. President Thomas&nbsp;S. Monson said: &ldquo;Pornography is especially dangerous and addictive. Curious exploration of pornography can become a controlling habit, leading to coarser material and to sexual transgression. Avoid pornography at all costs&rdquo; (&ldquo;Preparation Brings Blessings,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign</span> or <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> May 2010, 65).</p>
					<p>&ldquo;Extremely alarming &hellip; are the reports of the number of individuals who are utilizing the Internet for evil and degrading purposes, the viewing of pornography being the most prevalent of these purposes. My brothers and sisters, involvement in such will literally destroy the spirit. Be strong. Be clean. Avoid such degrading and destructive types of content at all costs&mdash;wherever they may be! I sound this warning to everyone, everywhere&rdquo; (&ldquo;Until We Meet Again,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign</span> or <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> May 2009, 113).</p>
					<p>&ldquo;Avoid any semblance of pornography. It will desensitize the spirit and erode the conscience. We are told in the Doctrine and Covenants, &lsquo;That which doth not edify is not of God, and is darkness&rsquo; [<a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/50.23?lang=eng#22" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 50:23</a>]&rdquo; (&ldquo;True to the Faith,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign</span> or <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> May 2006, 18&ndash;19).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="18-10711_000_036"><a name="18-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote18-10711_000_036">18.</a></span>
					<p>See David&nbsp;A. Bednar, <span class="emphasis">Act in Doctrine</span> (2012), 53.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="19-10711_000_036"><a name="19-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote19-10711_000_036">19.</a></span>
					<p>See Dallin&nbsp;H. Oaks, <span class="crossRef"><no-search id="25911_000_010"></no-search>&ldquo;Priesthood Authority in the Family and the Church,&rdquo;</span><span class="emphasis"> Ensign</span> or <span class="emphasis">Liahona,</span> Nov. 2005, 24&ndash;27.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="20-10711_000_036"><a name="20-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote20-10711_000_036">20.</a></span>
					<p>Personal email, Aug. 5, 2013; see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/james/5.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">James 5:14</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="21-10711_000_036"><a name="21-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote21-10711_000_036">21.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/heb/5.4?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Hebrews 5:4</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="22-10711_000_036"><a name="22-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote22-10711_000_036">22.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/ot/isa/55.8?lang=eng#7" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Isaiah 55:8</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="23-10711_000_036"><a name="23-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote23-10711_000_036">23.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/4.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Jacob 4:13</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="24-10711_000_036"><a name="24-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote24-10711_000_036">24.</a></span>
					<p>See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/81.4-5?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 81:4&ndash;5</a>. President Gordon&nbsp;B. Hinckley said: &ldquo;Your obligation is as serious in your sphere of responsibility as is my obligation in my sphere. No calling in this church is small or of little consequence&rdquo; (&ldquo;This Is the Work of the Master,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign,</span> May 1995, 71).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="25-10711_000_036"><a name="25-10711_000_036">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote25-10711_000_036">25.</a></span>
					<p>M.&nbsp;Russell Ballard, &ldquo;Strength in Counsel,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign,</span> Nov. 1993, 76.</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
                                        
